        "goseg/handler/upload.go uses a package-global mutable dependency (`var defaultUploadService UploadService`) that can be replaced via `SetUploadService`, creating hidden runtime coupling through shared state rather than explicit wiring.",
        "goseg/handler/upload.go binds the handler boundary directly to importer-domain command construction (`importer.OpenUploadEndpointCmd`), so API-handler changes and importer contract changes are tightly coupled.",
        "goseg/startram/errors.go introduces a package-local boundary/error wrapper (`maskedWrappedError`, `wrapAPIConnectionError`) instead of using a shared cross-package boundary contract, reinforcing fragmented edge-policy patterns."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "confidence": "high"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "fragmented_boundary_policy",
      "summary": "Cross-module boundary policies are implemented ad hoc per package, creating inconsistent coupling patterns and hidden integration costs.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/handler/upload.go",
        "goseg/startram/errors.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "upload.go uses a mutable package-level service locator (`defaultUploadService` + `SetUploadService`) to coordinate dependencies.",
        "errors.go defines a custom package-local wrapping/redaction boundary (`maskedWrappedError`) for external API failures.",
        "Both files implement edge-boundary behavior locally with different mechanisms, indicating no shared architectural contract for dependency injection and boundary error semantics."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define a shared boundary pattern for edge modules: constructor-injected dependencies (no package-global mutation) plus a common boundary error contract/utilities package for redaction and wrapping. Migrate handler/startram edges to that contract and remove ad hoc local patterns.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "missing_shared_boundary_contract"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "upload_handler_global_mutable_dependency",
      "summary": "Upload handler relies on mutable global service state, creating order-dependent behavior across modules.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/handler/upload.go",
        "goseg/startram/errors.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "upload.go declares `var defaultUploadService UploadService = importerUploadService{}` and allows runtime replacement via `SetUploadService`.",
        "Handler execution (`UploadHandler`) reads this global directly, so behavior depends on who last mutated shared package state.",
        "Compared with startram/errors.go's pure function-style wrapper (`wrapAPIConnectionError(err)`), this mutable approach introduces broader cross-module side-effect risk."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace `SetUploadService`/global state with explicit dependency injection (e.g., a handler struct receiving `UploadService`), and pass that dependency from composition root to eliminate shared mutable coordination.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "missing_shared_boundary_contract"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "No unified architectural contract for module boundaries (dependency wiring + boundary error semantics).",
      "Reliance on package-local patterns encourages drift and uneven coupling decisions."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "upload_handler_global_mutable_dependency"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": []
  }
}


